  <div class="article-byline__content">
      <div class="article-byline__written-by">
    <strong>Written by</strong> <strong><script>function ga4_link112() { window.dataLayer.push(JSON.parse('{"event":"default_event"}')) }</script><a href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/authors/lily-hartman" onclick="ga4_link112()">Lily Hartman</a></strong>, staff writer, research expert, and active lifestyle enthusiast.
  </div>



    <p class="article-byline__pub-dates">
      Updated February  1, 2024
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

              <p></p>
<p>Whether you work from home or commute, adding a treadmill to your office setup can lead to a healthier lifestyle, especially if you normally sit at a desk all day. These machines can improve your cardiovascular health, alleviate lower back pain, and boost your energy level so you can tackle that next big work project.</p>

<p>If you’re ready to add a good daily walk or some light jogging to your office fitness routine, you’re in the right place. Here are the best under-desk treadmills to shop online now.
</p>
<div data-ga4-location="product_widget" data-product-widget data-label="" data-name="LifeSpan Fitness Omni Console" data-nav_ignore="" data-target_id="lifespan-fitness-tr1200-dt7-treadmill-desk-review" class="c-product-widget c-product-widget" id="lifespan-fitness-tr1200-dt7-treadmill-desk-review">
  <div class="c-product-widget__product">
      <div class="c-product-widget__vanity-container">
        <img alt="Product image of LifeSpan Fitness Omni Console" eager="false" class="lazyload blur-up " data-src="https://reviewed-com-res.cloudinary.com/image/fetch/s--IGV92ROw--/b_white,c_fit,cs_srgb,f_auto,fl_progressive.strip_profile,g_center,h_150,q_auto,w_375/https://reviewed-production.s3.amazonaws.com/1706748942357/lifespan.png" style="aspect-ratio: 0.53;" src="https://reviewed-com-res.cloudinary.com/image/fetch/s--Mu5drII5--/b_white,c_fit,cs_srgb,f_auto,fl_progressive.strip_profile,g_center,h_150,q_1,w_375/https://reviewed-production.s3.amazonaws.com/1706748942357/lifespan.png">
      </div>

<p></p>
<div class="c-product-widget__text-container">
      <div class="u2 c-product-widget__name">
        LifeSpan Fitness Omni Console
      </div>

<p></p>
<div class="c-product-widget__content">
      <ul>
<li>
<strong>Max speed:</strong> Up to 4 mph</li>
<li>
<strong>Weight limit:</strong> 350 lbs</li>
</ul>

<p>This portable, lightweight under-desk treadmill is easy to move to the corner of your home office at any time. And at just 7.25 inches high, it’s designed to squeeze into tight storage spaces. It offers a variety of speed settings, from 0.6 to 4 miles per hour, and LifeSpan calls its powerful motor “ultra-quiet.”</p>

<p>This model comes fully assembled, so there’s no installation process to worry about, and it allows you to input some of your personal preferences to customize your experience. As for safety features, you don’t have to worry about injuring yourself on the job; its auto-pause sensors will stop the belt from running anytime you get interrupted and have to pause your walk to answer an urgent email.</p>

<p></p>
</div>
    </div>
  </div>

<p></p>
<div class="pros-cons">
    <div class="pros">
      <h4 class="pros-cons__title">Pros</h4>
      <ul class="pros-cons__list">
          <li class="pros-cons__list-item">
            <p class="pros-cons__text">
              No installation required
            </p>

<p></p>
</li>
          <li class="pros-cons__list-item">
            <p class="pros-cons__text">
              Quiet operation
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="pros-cons__list-item">
            <p class="pros-cons__text">
              Auto-pause belt
            </p>
          </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

<p></p>
<div class="cons">
      <h4 class="pros-cons__title">Cons</h4>
      <ul class="pros-cons__list">
          <li class="pros-cons__list-item">
            <p class="pros-cons__text">
              A little pricey
            </p>

<p></p>
</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

<p></p>
